<h3>Key Points:</h3>
<ul>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Order: The highest derivative in t=
he equation determines the order.</li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Degree: The power of the highest d=
erivative (after removing any radicals or fractions).</li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Solution: A function (or set of fu=
nctions) that satisfies the differential equation.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Real-World Analogy</h3>
<p style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Imagine you're tracking the speed o=
f a car as it moves along a road. The car's speed at any moment depends on =
its acceleration (how quickly the speed changes). A differential equation c=
an model this relationship, helping predict future speed based on current a=
cceleration.</p>
