<h4>Applications in Physics</h4>
<ul>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Newton's Law of Cooling: Describes=
 temperature change over time.</li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Harmonic Motion: Models oscillatio=
ns like springs and pendulums.</li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Circuit Analysis: Describes curren=
t and voltage in electrical circuits.</li>
</ul>
<h4>What Are Ordinary Differential Equations Used for in Physics?</h4>
<p style=3D"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">ODEs are used to model physical sys=
tems where the change in a quantity depends on that quantity itself and pos=
sibly time. For example, they describe how a particle moves under the influ=
ence of forces, how a capacitor charges and discharges, and how populations=
 grow or decay.</p>
